context: On <a3_0>23 September 1946<a3_0/>, an 8,000-strong railroad worker strike began in Pusan. Civil disorder spread throughout the country in what became known as <a0_0>the Autumn uprising<a0_0/>. On 1 October <a1_0>1946<a1_0/>, Korean police killed three students in the Daegu Uprising; protesters counter-attacked, killing 38 policemen. On 3 October, some <a2_0>10,000<a2_0/> people attacked the Yeongcheon police station, killing three policemen and injuring some 40 more; elsewhere, some 20 landlords and pro-Japanese South Korean officials were killed.
